[[File:Fighting the Crazy archaeologist.png|thumb|300px|A player fights Bellock, the crazy archaeologist.]]
The crazy archaeologist is a relatively simple boss, but a simple mistake can cause some damage to you with his area of effect attack.

The most effective way is to use [[Magic]] while [[Protect from Missiles|Protecting from Missiles]] and avoiding his area of effect attack. His area of effect attack casts 3 books into the air that slowly land and hit a 3x3 area. This area is centred around where the books land. It is preceded by the crazy archaeologist yelling "''Rain of knowledge!''".

It is recommended to bring low value gear such as [[monk robes]] for [[Prayer]] bonus as even with the crazy archaeologist's somewhat high Magic defence, his Magic level is negligible, and thus is weak to Magic and your own Magic accuracy matters little. This is because Magic defence is calculated primarily based on one's Magic level.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/636095399070158848|date=25 August 2015|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/107525|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=NPCs' magic defence is calculated off their Magic level, not their Defence level, and his is negligible.}}

While you can melee him, he will start using melee attacks in addition to ranged ones when you are close. This extra damage, along with a shorter reaction time to the "''Rain of knowledge!"'' attack means you will need to resupply more often and have less supplies for player killers.

Alternatively the crazy archaeologist can be killed without taking damage. This can be done by luring him behind the obstacles to the north of the area, attacking him and quickly running back behind the obstacle (flinching).

==Suggested skills==
*{{SCP|Attack|50}} (if using [[Iban's staff (u)]])
*{{SCP|Prayer|40+}}
*{{SCP|Magic|75+}}

==Equipment==
The setup primarily consists of only '''taking 3 or 4 expensive items''' as this boss is located in the [[Wilderness]] with the possibility of [[player killers]] appearing. Although the crazy archaeologist is within the teleport range in the Wilderness (up to level 30 Wilderness), you may get [[teleblock]]ed. Untradeable items such as [[god capes]] are lost upon death above level 20 Wilderness if not protected. The crazy archeologist wanders around level 22 and 25 of the Wilderness.

With a [[powered staff]], a magic boost such as [[Magic potion]], [[Forgotten brew]], or [[Saturated heart|Saturated]] or [[Imbued heart]] will provide a bigger damage increase than additional magic damage gear.

